<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0014" sponsor="A. Cory Maloy" designation="HB" otherSponsor="Todd Weiler" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL0423" date="12/4/2025 12:12:387" printDate="12-04 12:05" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>3</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="A" src="code" buid="1" uid="C63I-1-S258_2026050620260506" fromuid="C63I-1-S258_2025100120250507" sort="63I01 02580020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">63I-1-258</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="2" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Behavior Analyst Licensing Amendments</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: A. Cory Maloy</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: Todd Weiler</otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><cn numlevel="1" lineno="4" slineno="0-4">Committee Note:<comrec voteid="37614" comcode="INTBUS" numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5"> The Business and Labor Interim Committee recommended this bill.<legvote numlevel="1" lineno="6" slineno="0-6">Legislative Vote:<yes>10 voting for</yes><no>0 voting against</no><abs>10 absent</abs></legvote></comrec></cn><gdhead lineno="7">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8">This bill extends the sunset date for the Behavior Analyst Licensing Act.</gd><hphead lineno="9">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11" level="1">extends the sunset date of the Behavior Analyst Licensing Act to July 1, 2036; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" level="1">makes technical changes.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="14">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="15" slineno="0-15">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="16">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="17" slineno="0-17">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saamd numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18"><snhead>AMENDS:</snhead><sn num="63I-1-258" src="code" uid="C63I-1-S258_2026050620260506" buid="1" sort="63I01 02580020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19"><bold>63I-1-258</bold>, as last amended by Laws of Utah 2025, Chapter 236</sn></saamd></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="20"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="63I-1-258" type="amend" src="code" uid="C63I-1-S258_2026050620260506" sort="63I01 02580020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="22" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section number="63I-1-258" numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="1-2" type="amend"><secline lineno="22">Section 1. Section <bold>63I-1-258</bold> is amended to read:</secline><catline lineno="23"><bold>63I-1-258<parens/>. Repeal dates: Title 58.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="1-null-1" dnum="1-o" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-3" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display>(1)</display>Title <xref depth="1" refnumber="58-13">58, Chapter 13</xref>, Health Care Providers Immunity from Liability Act, is repealed <ln numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-4"/>July 1, 2026.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-2" dnum="2-o:_-i" numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-5" ea="erase" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="2" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1001" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="5" groupid="5" style="2" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" deltag="end">Title 58, Chapter 15, Health Facility Administrator Act, is repealed July 1, 2035.</amend><amendoutend style="2"/></subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-3" dnum="3-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="27" slineno="1-6" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1002" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(3)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(2)</amend></display>Title <xref depth="1" refnumber="58-20b">58, Chapter 20b</xref>, Environmental Health Scientist Act, is repealed July 1, 2028.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-4" dnum="4-o:3-i" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-7" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1003" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(4)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(3)</amend></display>Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="58-37-3.5">58-37-3.5</xref>, Drugs for behavioral health treatment, is repealed July 1, 2027.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-5" dnum="5-o:4-i" numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-8" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1004" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(5)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(4)</amend></display>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-37-6(7)(f)(iii)">58-37-6(7)(f)(iii)</xref>, regarding a seven-day opiate supply restriction, is <ln numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-9"/>repealed July 1, 2032.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-6" dnum="6-o:5-i" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-10" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1005" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(6)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1006" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(5)</amend></display>Title <xref depth="1" refnumber="58-40">58, Chapter 40</xref>, Recreational Therapy Practice Act, is repealed July 1, 2033.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-7" dnum="7-o:6-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-11" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1006" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(7)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1007" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(6)</amend></display>Title <xref depth="1" refnumber="58-41">58, Chapter 41</xref>, Speech-Language Pathology and Audiology Licensing Act, is <ln numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="1-12"/>repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-8" dnum="8-o:7-i" numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="1-13" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1007" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(8)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1008" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(7)</amend></display>Title <xref depth="1" refnumber="58-46a">58, Chapter 46a</xref>, Hearing Instrument Specialist Licensing Act, is repealed July <ln numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="1-14"/>1, 2033.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-9" dnum="9-o:8-i" numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="1-15" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1008" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(9)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1009" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(8)</amend></display>Title <xref depth="1" refnumber="58-47b">58, Chapter 47b</xref>, Massage Therapy Practice Act, is repealed July 1, 2034.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-10" dnum="10-o:9-i" numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="1-16" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1009" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(10)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1010" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(9)</amend></display>Subsection <xref refnumber="58-47b-102(8)" depth="4">58-47b-102(8)</xref>, defining massage assistant, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-11" dnum="11-o:10-i" numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="1-17" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1010" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(11)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1011" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(10)</amend></display>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-47b-102(9)">58-47b-102(9)</xref>, defining massage assistant-in-training, is repealed <ln numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="1-18"/>July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-12" dnum="12-o:11-i" numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="1-19" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1011" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(12)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1012" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(11)</amend></display>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-47b-302(1)">58-47b-302(1)</xref>, regarding applicant for a massage <ln numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="1-20"/>assistant-in-training, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-13" dnum="13-o:12-i" numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="1-21" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1012" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(13)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1013" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(12)</amend></display>Subsection <xref refnumber="58-47b-302(2)" depth="4">58-47b-302(2)</xref>, regarding applicant for a massage assistant, is <ln numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="1-22"/>repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-14" dnum="14-o:13-i" numlevel="1" lineno="44" slineno="1-23" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1013" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(14)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1014" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(13)</amend></display>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-47b-303(3)(b)">58-47b-303(3)(b)</xref>, regarding expiration of a massage <ln numlevel="1" lineno="45" slineno="1-24"/>assistant-in-training license, is repealed July 1, 2029.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-15" dnum="15-o:14-i" numlevel="1" lineno="46" slineno="1-25" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1014" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(15)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1015" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(14)</amend></display>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="58-55-201(2)">58-55-201(2)</xref>, regarding the Alarm System and Security Licensing <ln numlevel="1" lineno="47" slineno="1-26"/>Advisory Board, is repealed July 1, 2027.</subsection><subsection ssid="1-null-16" dnum="16-o:15-i" numlevel="1" lineno="48" slineno="1-27" level="1"><display><amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="1015" style="2" owner="o" level="1" deltag="both">(16)</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1016" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="both" space="true">(15)</amend></display>Title <xref depth="2" refnumber="58-61-7">58, Chapter 61, Part 7</xref>, Behavior Analyst Licensing Act, is repealed <amendoutstart style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="erase" pairid="4" groupid="4" style="2" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" deltag="both">July 1, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="49" slineno="1-28"/>2026</amend><amendoutend style="2"/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="3" groupid="3" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" 